Relativistic electron precipitation structures are categorized (e.g., Nakamura et al. 2000, see their Fig. 1) as “broad precipitation” covering the entire outer radiation belt (L-shells between ∼3 and 6), “precipitation bands” (PBs) across ΔL∼0.5-1\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
